🧠 Multimodal Reasoning Agent Platform
📌 Overview

This project is a multimodal AI system that interprets images and natural language prompts to produce structured, actionable JSON outputs.

Unlike simple captioning tools, this system focuses on:

Understanding what is in an image
Interpreting what the user actually wants
Performing reasoning over both inputs
Producing validated structured outputs for real applications

It is designed as a modular AI system, separating:

Application backend (Node.js + MongoDB)
AI reasoning engine (Python + LLM workflow)
User interface (React)
🎯 Problem It Solves

Most AI vision models today:

Describe images but don’t take action
Fail to generalize beyond fixed tasks
Produce unstructured text that is hard to integrate

This system solves that by transforming images into:

📊 structured data
⚙️ automation-ready outputs
🧩 decision support artifacts
