🧠 Core Design Principle
❌ Not a classifier system

This project does NOT rely on fixed labels like:

Receipt
Whiteboard
Product
✅ Instead: Dynamic understanding

The system interprets:

Image content
User intent
Required output format

This makes it extensible to any visual reasoning task.

🔄 AI Workflow Pipeline
1. Input Stage

User provides:

Image (receipt, slide, note, product, etc.)
Text prompt (e.g. “Analyze this”)
2. Understanding Stage

The AI first builds a structured understanding:

{
  "image_type": "unknown/general",
  "observations": [],
  "user_goal": "inferred goal",
  "task_type": "extraction | reasoning | decision"
}
3. Vision Processing

The model extracts:

Objects
Text (OCR-like reasoning)
Layout structure
Context clues
4. Reasoning Layer

The system determines:

What the user wants
What is relevant in the image
What should be ignored
5. Multi-Agent Processing

Instead of a single model call:

Vision Agent → understands image
Reasoning Agent → interprets intent
Critic Agent → checks correctness
Formatter Agent → enforces JSON schema
6. Validation Layer

All outputs are validated using schemas:

Ensures JSON correctness
Prevents hallucinated fields
Enforces structure consistency
7. Output Stage

Final response:

{
  "result": {},
  "confidence": 0.87,
  "needs_review": false
}
